description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Are you &lt;/em&gt;a highly motivated and experienced Advanced Clinical Practitioner (ACP) ?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to live and work in beautiful Dorset? Dorset provides a superb opportunity to enjoy a life amid the outstanding areas of natural beauty both in the countryside and along the stunning coast line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a skilled ACP into a new and exciting integrated approach with local PCNs We are offering an opportunity for an ACP to be involved in a truly integrated way of working to deliver high quality health care for those patients with a high level of frailty or complex long term conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Network you will be joining a multi-disciplinary service to promote admission avoidance and proactive Advanced Care Planning . You will be working with the team in service delivery, triaging and prioritising patient need to achieve our overall objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ACP will be based in Bournemouth, working flexibly across sites. You will provide advanced clinical advice, leadership and support ensuring the needs of the service are met by exercising and demonstrating high levels of clinical judgement, critical analysis and advanced decision making skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally, the successful candidate will be an independent non-medical prescriber or willing to complete this training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hours will be full time at 37.5 per week but may be scheduled over an 8am-8pm with a possible future weekend rota as the role develops.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we can also offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated career pathways and great opportunities for continuing professional development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continued Leadership development and training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent support from Consultants, GPs and Advanced Practitioners working within the hub and Primary Care Networks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension scheme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discount and salary sacrifice scheme..&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check. The DBS levies a charge of £40 and the Trust will recover this cost in instalments from your first 3 salary payments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants who subscribe to the DBS update service and are able to present a valid DBS certificate will not incur a charge&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are interested in moving to Dorset we also offer a generous relocation package of up to £5,000. For further details on relocation expenses please email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;dhc.careers@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:  Alison Tallant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title:  Locality Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:  alison.tallant1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:  07890327342&lt;/p&gt;
